HEADWORD: Interramal
<hw>In`ter*ra"mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>inter-</ets> + L. <ets>ramus</ets> a branch.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Between rami or branches; esp., between the
mandibles, or rami of the lower jaw; intermandibular.</def>⟦br⟧
